OL,5,GRising energy bills are forcing
OL,6,Gbusinesses as well as consumers to
OL,7,Gthink about their electricity use.
OL,9,FThere are no legal caps on the
OL,10,Fpotential increases facing businesses 
OL,11,Fconsumers do at least have some
OL,12,Fprotection from Ofgem caps although
OL,13,Fthis will offer little comfort to those
OL,14,Fon a tight income. So might
OL,15,Fbroadcasters be affected?
OL,17,FThe BBC cash crisis of 1975 led to many
OL,18,Fcuts. The least painful cut was
OL,19,Fdirectly linked to rising electricity
OL,20,Fprices and the need to save energy.
OL,3,CEnergy price crisis: time to review
OL,4,Ctransmitter usage?
